feat(frontend): landing page, voice-to-text, dark mode polish, PWA icons, html2canvas-pro fix

Major additions:
- Landing page at / with hero, feature cards, demo-prompt links,
  architecture section, and footer. Chat moved to /chat.
- Voice-to-text on InputBar via Web Speech API (id-ID locale).
  Mic button appears only when browser supports SpeechRecognition.
- PWA icons generated from the SVG logo (icon-192.png maskable,
  icon-512.png any). Manifest now resolves all icon references.

Dark mode polish (FP-3.2 backfill):
- MessageBubble: assistant fallback bubble gets dark:bg-[#1E293B]
  dark:border-[#334155] dark:text-[#F1F5F9]. User bubble gets
  dark:bg-[#2563EB] for contrast.
- InputBar: textarea, wrapper, send button, and hint text all get
  dark: class pairs. Voice mic button has red pulse when active.

Bug fix:
- html2canvas 1.x cannot parse oklab/oklch color functions that
  Tailwind 4 emits. Swapped to html2canvas-pro 2.x (drop-in fork
  that handles modern CSS color spaces). Removed html2canvas from
  deps.

Other:
- ChatWindow reads ?prompt= from URL and auto-sends on mount
  (landing page demo-prompt links use this).
- /chat/page.tsx wrapped in Suspense + force-dynamic for
  useSearchParams compatibility.
- .vscode/settings.json change (auto-generated by IDE, harmless).
